definition.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which the sulfhydryl group of a cysteine residue at the active center acts as a nucleophile.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of nonterminal peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism using a cysteine residue at the enzyme active center, and requiring the presence of calcium.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which water acts as a nucleophile, one or two metal ions hold the water molecule in place, and charged amino acid side chains are ligands for the metal ions.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a catalytic mechanism that involves a catalytic triad consisting of a serine nucleophile that is activated by a proton relay involving an acidic residue (e.g. aspartate or glutamate) and a basic residue (usually histidine).
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of internal peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which the hydroxyl group of a threonine residue at the active center acts as a nucleophile.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (3S)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA -eq- trans-2-enoyl-CoA + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an epoxide + H2O -eq- a glycol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  estradiol-17-beta + NADP+ -eq- estrone + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + estrone -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + estrone 3-sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + ethanolamine -eq- ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphoethanolamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CTP + ethanolamine phosphate -eq- diphosphate + CDP-ethanolamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CDP-ethanolamine + 1,2-diacylglycerol -eq- CMP + a phosphatidylethanolamine.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alpha-(2--gt-3)-, alpha-(2--gt-6)-, alpha-(2--gt-8)-glycosidic linkages of terminal sialic residues in oligosaccharides, glycoproteins, glycolipids, colominic acid and synthetic substrates.
Catalysis of the reaction -  polyphosphate(n) + H2O -eq- polyphosphate(n-1) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 farnesyl diphosphate -eq- diphosphate + presqualene diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-trans,6-trans-farnesyl diphosphate + isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- diphosphate + geranylgeranyl diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + n malonyl-CoA + 2n NADPH + 2n H+ -eq- long-chain fatty acid + n+1 CoA + n CO2 + 2n NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + [acyl-carrier protein] -eq- CoA + acetyl-[acyl-carrier protein].
Catalysis of the reaction -  malonyl-CoA + [acyl-carrier protein] -eq- CoA + malonyl-[acyl-carrier protein].
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + malonyl-[acyl-carrier protein] -eq- 3-oxoacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + CO2 + [acyl-carrier protein].
Catalysis of the reaction -  (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NADP+ -eq- 3-oxoacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (3R)-3-hydroxypalmitoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] -eq- 2-hexadecenoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NAD+ -eq- trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NADP+ -eq- trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  oleoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + H2O -eq- [acyl-carrier protein] + oleate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + n malonyl-CoA + 2n NADH + 2n NADPH + 4n H+ -eq- a long-chain acyl-CoA + n CoA + n CO2 + 2n NAD+ + 2n NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4 Fe2+ + 4 H+ + O2 -eq- 4 Fe3+ + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  reduced ferredoxin + NADP+ -eq- oxidized ferredoxin + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  protoheme -eq- Fe(2+) + protoporphyrin IX.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + tetrahydrofolyl-(Glu)(n) + L-glutamate -eq- ADP + phosphate + tetrahydrofolyl-(Glu)(n+1).
Catalysis of the reaction -  formamide + H(2)O -eq- formate + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + formate + tetrahydrofolate -eq- ADP + phosphate + 10-formyltetrahydrofolate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-fructose 2,6-bisphosphate + H2O -eq- D-fructose-6-phosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-fructose 1,6-bisphosphate -eq- glycerone phosphate + D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-malate -eq- fumarate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-fumarylacetoacetate + H(2)O -eq- acetoacetate + fumarate + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-galactose + ATP -eq- alpha-D-galactose 1-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine + H2O -eq- D-galactose + N-acylsphingosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  geranyl diphosphate + isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- 2-trans,6-trans-farnesyl diphosphate + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the successive hydrolysis of beta-D-glucose units from the non-reducing ends of (1--gt-3)-beta-D-glucans, releasing alpha-glucose.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal (1--gt-4)-linked alpha-D-glucose residues successively from non-reducing ends of the chains with release of beta-D-glucose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + D-glucose -eq- ADP + D-glucose-6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucono-1,5-lactone + H2O -eq- D-gluconate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + H(2)O -eq- beta-D-fructose 6-phosphate + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + acetyl-CoA -eq- N-acetyl-D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucose + acceptor -eq- D-glucono-1,5-lactone + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucose 6-phosphate + NADP+ -eq- D-glucono-1,5-lactone 6-phosphate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucopyranose 6-phosphate + H2O -eq- D-glucose + phosphate. D-glucopyranose is also known as D-glucose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucose 6-phosphate -eq- D-fructose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine + H2O -eq- D-glucose + N-acylsphingosine.
